  "parent": "cel",
  "notes": "Common Brythonic / Proto-Brythonic. Celtic language of pre-Roman and Roman Britain. Ancestor of Welsh, Cornish, Breton. Substrate in English: place names (London, Thames, Kent, Dover), possibly influence on English phonology. Voiceless lateral /ɬ/ and voiceless rhotic /r̥/ are diagnostic features. Refs: Jackson (1953), Schrijver (1995).",
